 you <a class="challenge_1" href="tryout.php" target="_blank">click on this link</a>, you'll get an image with a certain amount of points.
Your job is to find the circle with the smallest area in such a way, that all points are either inside this circle or on the boundary of the circle.
When you find this circle, round the x and y coordinates of the center of the circle to 5 decimals, add them together, and add the radius of the circe, also rounded to 5 decimals, to this number.
<br/><br/>
To summarize the rules:<br/>
<center>
<table border=0 style='color: white;'>
	<tr>
		<td>1.</td>
		<td>The point 0,0 is located in the topleft corner</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>2. </td>
		<td>1 Unit = 1 Pixel</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>3. </td>
		<td>You need to find the smallest circle enclosing all the points</td>
	</tr>
</table>
</center>
<br/>
Submit this number to <p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">&quot;http://bright-shadows.net/challenges/programming/inferno_circle/solution.php?solution=&quot;+number</p>You have 3 seconds to do this challenge.
<div class="challenge_mono_1" style="text-align:center;"><pre style="margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:10pt;">
